column5: We have had some crazy clippers go through here all night and still going on.Foot of powder and north winds.The wind is still gusting at times which will makes visability, nil at times. Radio says hiway 400 snow covered with drift areas.  Carefull out there guys and gals if your heading to IBP.Lots of snow covered holes out there now.  Have fun and play safe.
thank you Brian  we will be careful  snowing here pretty good too
These clips are nuts bud.One minute it clear,next ya cant see yer nose.You going to catch a fish today?   Have fun.
well Lloyd is with me so I will not catch anything  I have to move at least a km away form him to be successful .....
Just move near me Terry, you'll get some
dang, I didn't see that till I got home.....dang dang..LOL
Very windy and very snowy today, hauling the hut in 1.5ft of powder really sucked.   Not to many people out there for a weekend (at least where I was)
How did everyone make out? Anyone having a fish supper?
Perch..  To many perch.  It was a fun day though.  I love the cold, windy stuff.  Makes me feel like an eskimo!
I got about half a dozen herring, 4-5 smelts for spring pike and lost a 8-10lb laker right at the hole.   Not a bad day, but far from great.
